This paper focuses on sarcasm detection in natural language processing, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of deep convolutional neural networks for feature extraction and classification suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the issue of generalizability, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social media analysis (cs.SI).
